channel.title: Delta
channel.description: I have a 317 delta and I'm trying to get it so other people can play it, whenever they try to play it, it says error connecting to server when they login, I have a no-ip IP, whenever I check to see if it's online it says online, but I don't think it downlaods the cache for them, so what do I do?

item.title: Delta
item.dc:creator: @NotLikingThis NotLikingThis
item.description:
@NotLikingThis wrote:

If it does not download the cache properly then send them the download link or above say “If the cache is not downloading properly, Click Here” or something like that. I used dropbox for my webhost before i started using Host Gator.
If it is not letting them connect but it is downloading the cache then make sure you are fully portforwarded and there is nothing blocking the ports.(Firewalls)
My friend had the same problem but when i used TeamViewer i found out that both his ports were not the same. His client had 5555 and his source had 43594 and he didn’t notice that…
